description.1: Will Doom's knowledge of science and sorcery be his saving grace? Or will an out-of-world being reveal Doom's true mettle? Enter the Beyonder!
description.2: SECRET WARS 2 To destroy the Beyonder, Rachel Summers must also take the lives of many others. Will she finally eliminate the Beyonder or let him live?
description.8: Luke, Leia, Han and their friends fly to Zeltros to enlist their aid in the war against the Nagai, only to have the war follow them!
description.9: To help Tigra get her feral side under control, the Avengers seek out the one man that may have answers - Jack Russell, AKA the Werewolf by Night!
description.11: Sunspot nearly snaps in his fallout from Secret Wars II. The Beyonder returns for Illyana Rasputin.
description.13: Karen Page sells Daredevil's secret identity for drugs. Then, Kingpin buys the name and proceeds to wreck Matt Murdock's life.
description.14: While Bruce Banner lies helpless in a coma, the Hulk is on a rampage! Can the Avengers defeat the Green Goliath? Meanwhile, Doc Samson makes capturing the Hulk his personal vendetta...
description.15: With the aid of Henry Pym, Iron Man must shrink to the size of an ant to recover his fortune lost in a bank's computer.
description.18: The First Appearance of X-Factor!  The original X-Men reunite as an all-new team with an all-new vision of how to achieve Professor Xavier's dream. The X-Factor legacy starts here!
description.20: A day at the salon comes to a halt for the Invisible Woman, She-Hulk and Marvel Girl, when Doctor Doom attacks the Latverian Embassy!
description.21: SECRET WARS 2 The Phoenix must kill...the Beyonder?!
description.23: In this volume's final issue, Captain Britain and friends track down a killer criminal!
description.24: The Puma wants to kill the Beyonder. But will Spidey let him?
description.25: Black Knight makes it a priority to study the erratic spikes in Wasp's powers. Meanwhile, a young woman steals Hank Pym's Yellowjacket suit and makes her own deadly modifications.
description.26: To aid Nighthawk, a meta-human from alternate dimension, Captain America rallies together the Avengers and the Fantastic Four to save the universe!
description.29: One of Wanda's incantations goes awry...transporting our heroine to the Land of the Dead! Quicksilver learns of his sister's happy news.
description.31: The Beyonder, fed up with being persecuted, decides to fight back. Marvel heroes witness the One from Beyond go beserk, as Molecule Man tries to locate the source of the Beyonder's rage. The origin of Beyonder-Realm revealed!
description.32: It's the bitter end for some of our grand Defenders! How many members will perish in an epic battle against the psychically deadly Moondragon?
description.33: LOVE AND WAR! After barely surviving an explosion, The Punisher gets caught in a gang war after he reveals to the press that he killed the Kingpin.
description.34: The entire planet is thrown into flux as Mojo arrives on Earth seeking worshippers. The master and his slave have a final confrontation in this concluding issue - don't miss Longshot Vs. Mojo!
description.35: Humanity quakes as Kro shores up his power! Ghaur is nowhere to be found, yet the Eternals still face exhausting odds. The Forgotten One enters the war.
description.41: SECRET WARS The Power Pack has defeated Kurse, but he is not finished just yet. Elsewhere in the city, Thor returns and undergoes a startling transformation.
description.43: The West Coast Avengers must team up with Firebird to face off with an all-new, all-deadly Marvel villain - Master Pandemonium!
description.46: The first battle between Captain America and Wolverine!  The Ultimate-Killing Robot, Tess-1, is after Cap! But when Wolverine appears, the villain decides he’s no longer just satisfied with only killing one hero!
description.47: It's confirmed- Scarlet Witch and Vision are expecting! But how is Doctor Strange involved?
description.49: The satanic Mephisto unites super villains from this dimension and the next to take down Beyonder. Will the Fantastic Four's Thing be the ally the Beyonder needs? The Thing gets some ultimate 'clobberin' time' as he takes down all of Marvel's baddies!
description.50: Returning to their headquarters, the Defenders find Manslaughter, an old foe, controlling their security systems! Meanwhile, Interloper has found the still-possessed Moondragon!
description.52: New traveling mate Ceci Ryder gets to hear the secret origin of Howard the Duck! Their adventure takes them to the center of the Earth, where they discover a hidden civilization. But will they make it out back to the surface alive!?
description.53: Punisher goes back to prison. In an attempt to find out who drugged him, Castle comes face-to-face with Jigsaw...and partners up with the warden!
description.54: Rita is held captive by Mojo and Spiral...in a ploy to find Longshot! Dejected and morose after the loss of his luck powers, Longshot seeks out Rita for support...but finds Doctor Strange instead!
description.55: His name is Slyde. He's out for revenge! Why? Against whom? And how can Spider-Man stop him when nothing, not even his web, can stick to Slyde?
description.56: Captain America, Wasp, and Black Knight must convince their federal sponsor, Raymond Sikorsky, that Namor is a worthy candidate for full membership. While observing the Wasp during a training session, Black Knight wonders if she might want to date him.
description.57: The Captain America Hot Line gets a call that really burns up the wires and the all-new Serpent Society take on an assassination contract in "Mission: Murder Modok!"
description.58: Leia alone on a world full of hostile aliens... and the only people she has to help her are four teenagers-and one badly wounded enemy!
description.64: Brian's sister Betsy takes up the mantle of Captain Britain in his stead!
description.65: Someone has captured Betsy Beatty and is trying to force the Gladiator back into a life of crime.
description.66: Doc Samson discovers a way to separate Bruce Banner from the Hulk. But when Banner is rendered into a coma, will Samson's full plan come to fruition?
description.67: Ka-Zar visits Iron Man and the West Coast Avengers.
description.68: The first appearance of Betsy Braddock as Psylocke.  Betsy's appearance undergoes a severe alteration at the hands of Mojo and Spiral. Plus, Cypher questions his existence as a mutant.
description.72: Captain America finds a mysterious woman in a pod below Jamaica Bay- could this young lady be the X-Men's long-lost Marvel Girl?
description.73: Who shall lead the X-Men? Storm and Cyclops duel to determine the answer!
description.82: The Deviant Navy has assembled, and Ikaris, with help from Makkari, squares off against Kro and his complete fleet! As the war for Earth continues, Thena makes an executive call as the Eternals’ true ruler!
description.83: Tigra embarks on a soul-searching journey to prove herself as an Avenger...but she finds herself the prey of Kraven the Hunter!
description.85: Thor and his fellow warriors are fleeing Hel when they are attacked yet again! At the Helgate the fellowship must do battle with the demons of Hel. And one of them must stand to defend Gjallerbru! Who shall it be?
description.87: The Vulture is back and preying on the grave of Heather Glenn! Plus, Nelson & Murdock out of business? Foggy hits Matt right where it hurts, when he blames Matt for their law practice's failure. Has Foggy reached the end of his rope?
description.88: The Green Goliath receives a less-than-warm welcome upon his return to Earth! Can Hulk escape a confrontation with Doc Samson?
description.89: The secret of Bethany Cabe revealed! The fate of Tony Stark determined! And, the Masque seeks revenge.
description.90: The true menace behind Karma's treachery is revealed. Which of the X-Men's classic foes is the true enemy?
description.93: This Secret Wars II tie-in portrays the Human Torch like he's never been seen before. Always known as Sue's kid brother, he'll be forced to grow up when his biggest fan is part of a confrontation with the Beyonder.
description.96: “Mutant mania is running wild!” This issue? A heavily censored preview of X-FACTOR.
description.97: Game, set, and match: the Deviants are eager and ready for war—and the Eternals are happy to oblige!

5.text: Simon Williams leaps off the page in his own one-shot adventure! Feeling dissatisfied as an Avenger, yet discouraged as an actor, Wonder Man tries a new occupation on for size: Simon Williams, science tech trouble-shooter! What does this position entail exactly? As Wonder Man straddles the line between civilian and hero, he’ll need to make his most difficult decision yet -- is he truly cut out to be one of Earth’s Mightiest?

6.text: What is the secret that powers all of Cashelot?

7.text: Planet Terry’s cosmic mission to find his parents ends here! After discovering the truth about his father, Terry sets off to recover his mother who believed he was lost at birth.

9.text: To help Tigra get her feral side under control, the Avengers seek out the one man that may have answers - Jack Russell, AKA the Werewolf by Night!

10.text: Doctor Strange must help a woman reclaim half her soul from Mephisto. How did this happen to Topaz? The Fantastic Four join the fray!

11.text: Sunspot nearly snaps in his fallout from Secret Wars II. The Beyonder returns for Illyana Rasputin.

12.text: Thor has been turned into a frog! Though he now may be an amphibian, he is still a warrior. And when struck by rats, the mighty frog Thor must return blows in kind-with leg and with tongue!
Thor has been turned into a frog! Though he now may be an amphibian, he is still a warrior. And when struck by rats, the mighty frog Thor must return blows in kind-with leg and with tongue!

16.text: Old members resign! New members join! The team moves into a new HQ! This is a whole new Squadron Supreme.

22.text: Secret Wars II crashes headlong into the life of Spider-Man! The Beyonder clashes with a mysteriously powered-up Puma, and Spider-Man needs to…stay out of the fight!?

27.text: The conclusion to Nightcrawler’s standalone mini! A prisoner of Shagreen once more, Nightcrawler finds that his swashbuckling adventure has run its course. Luckily, Magik and Kitty Pryde arrive to rescue our hero…and the Bamfs tag along too!

28.text: When Katie secretly invites a hoard of Power Pack's hero allies over for Thanksgiving dinner, things quickly spiral out of control…!

30.text: Who is Manglin' Mahoney? The Thing is about to find out in a sensational wrestling match!

37.text: A simple check-up goes crazy when the vet thinks Top Dog is contagious!

38.text: Terry’s ‘father’, Vermin the Vile, pushes his son over the edge when he forces the young spacefarer to carry out his evil deeds!

39.text: Someone is betraying the Avengers to their deadliest enemy, Agent Gyrich of the U.S. government! Who would dare? What lies has the traitor spread, and why? A shocking, suspense-filled saga unfolds!

41.text: SECRET WARS The Power Pack has defeated Kurse, but he is not finished just yet. Elsewhere in the city, Thor returns and undergoes a startling transformation.
SECRET WARS The Power Pack has defeated Kurse, but he is not finished just yet. Elsewhere in the city, Thor returns and undergoes a startling transformation.

42.text: Not only have the Frost Giants besieged the realm of Nornheim, they've made off his beloved Queen Karnilla as well! The journey through the Nine Worlds begins!

43.text: The West Coast Avengers must team up with Firebird to face off with an all-new, all-deadly Marvel villain - Master Pandemonium!

44.text: Adventure from Weirdworld! Tyndall and Velanna help Mud-Butt in a bar brawl, followed by much carousing and drink. But with Lord Raven hot on Mud-Butt’s trail, could this happy ending turn tragic? Featuring the Were-Men of Weirdworld! Plus, Carol Danvers explores her identity as Binary following the appointment of a new Captain Marvel.

45.text: Who is the Iron Man of the year 2020? Find out here, as Arno Stark hurtles into the past to prevent a nuclear explosion in his own time!

48.text: The Thing takes on the big screen—as a mighty movie producer! Plus, this set offers a chance to reunite with Sharon Ventura...

51.text: Strange people are trying to kidnap Dazzler and use her powers for their own twisted ends!

59.text: Secret Wars II tie-in! Upon their return from K'un-L'un, Luke and Danny realize that their prophetic dream about the Beyonder has actually come true…and now the Heroes for Hire HQ is solid gold!

61.text: When senior simians break bad, Peter Porker is there to retire them to jail! Plus, Thrr the God of Thunder!

62.text: The Royal Olympics Gold Medal is up for grabs and Roy has entered the contest!

63.text: Terry uncovers the identity of his father, and must prevent his dad’s death at the hands of Omnus!

69.text: The Institute of Evil has captured the Golden Archer and attempts to extract information about the Squadron Supreme with the help of Doctor Decibel's sonic device. What will they learn? Are the identities of the Squadron about to be reavealed?

74.text: The Death of Jean DeWolff CONCLUSION! The Sin-Eater's identity is revealed... but that sure doesn't stop him from continuing his plans! Who is next on the assailant's list? Shots are fired...but against who?!

75.text: Alien invaders come to Endor and capture foonars to use for harvesting the planet's trees. Can the Ewok's halt their devious plan?

76.text: Nightcrawler comes face-to-face with his living caricature. Meet the Bamfs, a strange race of mini-Nightcrawlers with teleportation powers and prehensile tails! Nightcrawler uncovers the truth about the dimension he’s trapped in. How is Kitty Pryde responsible for his current reality?

77.text: The Kurse is in New York looking for vengeance upon Thor!

78.text: Cloak and Dagger have their first encounter with The Beyonder, who, as usual wreaks havoc among their lives.

83.text: Tigra embarks on a soul-searching journey to prove herself as an Avenger...but she finds herself the prey of Kraven the Hunter!

84.text: Clea reigns over the Dark Dimension as its rightful queen. Meanwhile, The Beyonder threatens mankind, summoning Strange to action.

85.text: Thor and his fellow warriors are fleeing Hel when they are attacked yet again! At the Helgate the fellowship must do battle with the demons of Hel. And one of them must stand to defend Gjallerbru! Who shall it be?

86.text: HULK SMASH CANADA! The Jade Giant continues his rampage across the country, and only Alpha Flight stands in his way! Can Canada's best super-team defeat the STRONGEST THERE IS?

91.text: In "Change of Heart," a member of Squadron Supreme refuses to move forward with the plan to rule the planet. You'll never guess who it is!

95.text: The Death of Jean DeWolff PART 3! Spider-Man learns that the Sin-Eater was the one who killed Jean DeWolff. With the Sin-Eater still out on the loose can Spider-Man put an end to his reign before the next victim is claimed?

96.text: “Mutant mania is running wild!” This issue? A heavily censored preview of X-FACTOR.

99.text: Terry may have an unexpected reunion on Space Station W-22! But first, he’s got to survive!
